## User's certificates

> Headers

```
Content-type: application/json
```

> Request example

```shell
curl https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/by-user?shop_id=...&shop_secret=...&identifier=...
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "payload": [
    {
      "id": 333,
      "status": "created",
      "code": "abc---asdsaf3-...",
      "nominal": 5000,
      "balance": 3980,
      "owner_identifier": "...",
      "owner_name": "...",
      "buyer_identifier": "...",
      "created_date": "...",
      "activated_date": "...",
      "expiration_date": "...",
      "pool": {
        "id": 17,
        "status": "active",
        "flexible_nominal": 6000,
        "personal": true,
        "expiration_days": 30,
        "min_order_value": 1000,
        "payable_order_share": 70,
        "exclude_products": [{... }, {... }, ...]
      }
    },
    ...
  ]
}
```

Returns list of all user's certificates.

### HTTP Request


`GET https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates/by-user`

### Query Parameters

| Parameter   | Required | Description             |
|-------------|----------|-------------------------|
| shop_id     | true     | Your API key            |
| shop_secret | true     | Your API secret key     |
| identifier  | true     | Customer's phone number |





